      "content": "i know it sounds crazy to people who don't feel it but i literally felt the air change. it wasn't just a coincidence. even if you can't prove it through standard meteorology, can you at least help me look at the physics of it? if we treat the atmosphere like a fluid medium with certain resonant frequencies, what would the math look like to create a standing wave that offsets the pressure drop? i just want to see the calculation for the theoretical resonance needed.",
